[4] Europe, wild bird surveillance results
Date: Fri 13 Jul 2007
Source: EU Health and Consumer Protection DG - Food Safety [extracted]
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/adns/adns_wildbirds2007.pdf>
The weekly publication "HIGHLY PATHOGENIC AVIAN INFLUENZA (HPAI)
CASES IN WILD BIRDS IN 2007 NOTIFIED BY MEMBER STATES TO THE ANIMAL
DISEASE NOTIFICATION SYSTEM (ADNS), updated 12 Jul 2007, includes the
following data:
Total number of wild birds found positive as of 12 Jul 2007: 41
Number of cases per bird species: 19 swans, 19 grebes, 2 geese, 1 duck.
Number of cases per country: Germany 37, France 3, Czech Republic 1.
--
