[5] Bangladesh - Naogoan
Date: 13 Jul 2007
Source: The Daily Star
<http://www.thedailystar.net/2007/07/14/d70714013018.htm>

1500 fowls culled in Naogaon
------------------
Some 1500 domestic fowls were culled in the district town on Thursday
night [12 Jul 2007] following detection of avian influenza.
Two separate teams, led by a first class magistrate, searched local
houses at Pramanikpara, Mandolpara, Mollapara and Shibpur areas from
8:00 PM to midnight and culled the birds, district Livestock office
sources said.
Earlier, a sample of dead chicken was sent to Joypurhat Animal
Disease Laboratory for a test that detected the virus.
Later, the test result was sent to Bangladesh Livestock Research
Institute at Savar in Dhaka for confirmation.
On Thursday [12 Jul 2007], the deputy commissioner's office received
a faxed message from the institute, which said that poultry birds and
pigeons in the areas have been affected with bird flu.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall
[The most recent report to OIE from Bangladesh is dated 5 Jul 2007
and predates the onset of the above mentioned outbreak. In that
report, there is mention of 5 outbreaks -- 4 located in private farms
in Nilphamari District of Rajshahi Division, and one a farm in Dhaka
District of Dhaka Division, with dates of onset of these outbreaks in
May 2007. (see
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/reports/en_fup_0000005713_20070708_170937.pdf>
for full report).
Naogoan is located in Rajshahi Division in the northwest of
Bangladesh. Nilphamari is located to the north of Saidpur, a
significant distance from Naogoan where the current outbreak is
located. For a map of Bangladesh with Divisions, see
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/bangladesh_pol96.jpg>
-- to locate Nilphamari use the interactive map at
<http://encarta.msn.com/encnet/features/mapcenter/map.aspx?TextLatitude=25.767771967789468&TextLongitude=89.73156158691188&TextAltitude=10&TextSelectedEntity=23&MapStyle=Comprehensive&MapSize=Medium&MapStyleSelectedIndex=0&searchTextMap=Nilphamari+Bangladesh&MapStylesList=Comprehensive&ZoomOnMapClickCheck=on>
